  "text": "where \u00b5 0 is the low-field carrier mobility with the value of 1800 cm 2 /V\u00b7s for boron-doped diamond [CITATION_1] ; \u03b8 1 and \u03b8 2 are the fitting parameters that model the degradation of the carrier mobility due to the vertical field; V gt = V gs \u2212 V th . For the boron-doped C-H diamond, the Hall effect measurement shows that the hole mobility versus temperature can be approximated by \u00b5 \u221d T 1.2 [CITATION_2] . This positive relationship suggests that the temperature dependence of Hall mobility is due to the scattering of ionized impurities. Therefore, the temperature-dependent effective hole mobility is given by [CITATION_3] ",
